    <h2 class="normal mt4 mt5-ns  mb0">The Mountain</h2>
    <p class="lh-copy">Bill Smith led a group of 5 winemakers and grape growers to define what today is the Howell Mountain AVA. The AVA’s boundary starts at an elevation of 1400’ so even when it is cool and foggy on the valley floor, it is sunny and breezy up on the mountain. Randy was one of those pioneers and our wine epitomizes what has become synonymous with Howell Mountain Cabernet; deep concentration, bold, massive, ultra rich and elegant.</p>

		<blockquote class="mv4 mv5-ns  measure-narrow center">
		<p class="lh-copy i mb0">Howell Mountain grapes need thick skins to survive and thick skins provide deep flavors and chewy tannins.</p>
			<cite class="f6 f5-l ttu tracked tr db measure"> &mdash; James Laube</cite>
